<HEADLINE>
<P>
WAXING NOSTALGIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 We're in agreement with Mr. Hall's (TV Times, June 26) opinion that the older 
situation comedies are far superior to most of the current ones. We recently 
went to cable and thoroughly enjoy seeing again the older "Mary Tyler Moore," 
"Bob Newhart" and "Dick Van Dyke" shows. I had forgotten how genuinely funny 
they are. 
</P>
<P>
 Helen King, Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
