<HEADLINE>
<P>
BAITING FOR RATINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I can't imagine a newspaperman, when writing up an ongoing news event, saying, 
"We have just discovered a new twist on this item, so get the next edition for 
the full story."Yet on the TV channels, they do it all the time. The 4 o'clock 
news gives out blurbs about what's coming up at 5 o'clock, and at 5 o'clock, 
what's coming up at 6 or 11 -- no doubt to try and keep us watching. It seems 
to me what they, the station, already know at 4 o'clock should be shown or told 
at 4 o'clock. Then it would be, as they say, "News as it happens." 
</P>
<P>
 James Glen, Pacific Palisades 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
