imperfectly joined novellas. The students of the Arizona school strive to 
comprehend the loss of their friend as they struggle with usual teen-age 
crises. The teachers and administrators face problems of their own, but the two 
worlds don't quite mesh, and the resulting book is more notable for its flashes 
of insight than its successful examination of a sensitive subjective. 
