<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHANDLER PARODY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The 1994 International Imitation Raymond Chandler Writing Competition is being 
announced by Friends of the La Jolla Library.The object is to parody in 500 
words the writing style of the man who invented the hard-boiled whodunit and 
left the world the fictional character Philip Marlowe, a tough, witty and 
honorable detective. 
</P>
<P>
 The deadline for entries is Aug. 1. Prizes are $700 first, $500 second and 
$300 third. For details on entering, write to: Raymond Chandler Writing 
Competition, c/o Friends of the La Jolla Library, 3129 Bremerton Place, La 
Jolla, Calif. 92307. 
</P>
