<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94: QUARTERFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; TOO MUCH TIME ON THEIR HANDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 They can't tabulate World Cup statistics enough. A recent survey from Dallas 
reports that, while the German team stayed at the posh Mansion on Turtle Creek, 
the players demanded lots and lots of cornflakes. 
</P>
<P>
 The Germans, apparently, wolfed the flakes down by the caseload. 
</P>
<P>
 Also, in the 36 hours the Germans stayed at the mansion, they consumed 32 
cases of Perrier and six cases of apple juice. 
</P>
<P>
 The Saudis? Statistics now available reveal the Hotel Crescent Court in Dallas 
booked 36 rooms from the 49-man entourage. 
</P>
<P>
 Three of the rooms were set aside for prayer. Each player reportedly visited 
one of the three rooms daily to face Mecca. CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
