<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94: QUARTERFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; NOW IT COOLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL DWYRE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Weather played a big role in the Italy-Spain game. When the game began at 
noon, the sky was totally overcast, there was barely a breath of wind and the 
humidity was officially listed at 100%.By early in the second half, both teams 
were exhausted and Italy's coach, Arrigo Sacchi, even admitted that, while his 
game plan was to go all out for 90 minutes, his team just couldn't and was 
thoroughly outplayed after halftime by Spain. 
</P>
<P>
 About an hour after the game, the clouds lifted, the sun broke through and a 
light wind began breathing some life into the Foxboro area that had been, for 
Spain and Italy and 54,605 fans, a three-hour oven. BILL DWYRE 
</P>
