<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94: QUARTERFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; IN HARMONY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Past Dutch World Cup entrants have been criticized for being a collection of 
egos, rather than a team.But this squad is different, forward Marc Overmars 
insists. 
</P>
<P>
 "I hear (in 1990) there were a lot of problems, a lot of irritation, but this 
is very good. We are together now about five, six weeks and there are no 
problems at all," he said. "Let me give you an example. After training, when we 
are on the couches, sometimes we will sing songs together. It is true. Just 
little things like that show that we can be together and get along." 
</P>
<P>
 Even in defeat Saturday against Brazil. HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
