<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94: QUARTERFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; WORLD CUP 2, G-7 0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 There's a G-7 economic summit in Naples, but it comes in a distant second to 
the World Cup in importance. 
</P>
<P>
 And not only for Italians. 
</P>
<P>
 An aide whispered to Italian Premier Silvio Berlusconi that Dino Baggio had 
scored to give Italy a 1-0 lead over Spain as Berlusconi was rushing from a 
news conference Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 After answering questions for 45 minutes, Berlusconi met with Russian 
President Boris Yeltsin with the hope of rushing back for the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 French President Francois Mitterrand was trying to cut another news conference 
short, and when reporters persisted, he finally said to one, "You are no 
sportswoman." 
</P>
