<HEADLINE>
<P>
AMERICAN LEGION ROUNDUP; PITCHERS ON RUN TO EAST, WEST, NORTH, SOUTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It was a long day for pitchers Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Van Nuys East scored 18 runs in the second inning, then took the rest of the 
day off in an 18-1 victory over Burbank North in a District 20 game. 
</P>
<P>
 Not to be outdone, Woodland Hills West scored 16 runs in the second inning of 
a game against Granada Hills West. West settled for a 16-5 victory before 
coming back to win, 16-10, in the second game of a doubleheader. 
</P>
<P>
 Even North Hollywood (2-15) got into the act, trouncing Van Nuys South, 24-6, 
in the second game of a doubleheader after South won the opener, 14-4. 
</P>
<P>
 In other District 20 games: 
</P>
<P>
 Sun Valley 2-6, Sunland-Tujunga 1-1 -- Sam Viscarra drove in the winning run 
in the sixth inning of the opener. 
</P>
<P>
 Burbank South 2, Verdugo Hills 1 -- Eli Albertson doubled home Anthony 
Fabrizio with the winning run in the sixth. 
</P>
<P>
 Las Virgenes 9-4, Granada Hills East 3-2 -- Solid pitching by Brandon Cohen 
and Tanner Trosper gave Las Virgenes a sweep. 
</P>
<P>
 Valley North 13-0, Encino 3-2 -- Chris Hebert pitched a five-hit shutout and 
Encino (13-3) salvaged a split. Valley North (11-6) scored 10 runs in the first 
inning of the opener. 
</P>
</TEXT>
