<HEADLINE>
<P>
PHEBUS, AMPUERO GAIN TENNIS FINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Keri Phebus and Cecelia Ampuero of Newport Beach each won their semifinal 
matches Saturday, setting up an all-Orange County final today in the Toshiba 
Tennis Classic at the Rancho San Clemente Tennis and Fitness Club. 
</P>
<P>
 Ampuero, who is unseeded, easily defeated Lisa Alipaz of Anaheim, 6-3, 6-2. 
Phebus, who is seeded third, dominated her match against Rita Maria Pichardo of 
Cuba, 6-1, 6-1. 
</P>
<P>
 The winner of today's final will earn a berth in the qualifying tournament for 
the main draw of the Toshiba Tennis Classic, which features Steffi Graf, 
Arantxa Sanchez Vicario and Conchita Martinez. 
</P>
</TEXT>
