<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: FILM: JEFF BRIDGES TO GET STAR ON WALK OF FAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Actor Jeff Bridges, star of the summer action thriller "Blown Away" and 
three-time Academy Award nominee, will receive a star on the Hollywood Walk of 
Fame on Monday. The veteran actor will have his star placed next to that of his 
father, actor Lloyd Bridges. 
</P>
<P>
 Nominated for his first Oscar for Best Supporting Actor in Peter Bogdanovich's 
1971 film "The Last Picture Show," the 44-year-old thespian has starred in more 
than three dozen movies since his debut, at the age of four months, in "The 
Company She Keeps" with Jane Greer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
