<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: EDUCATION: WATANABE WINS TRUMAN SCHOLARSHIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 West Los Angeles resident Maika Watanabe, a student at Swarthmore College, has 
won the prestigious Truman Scholarship, given by the Harry S. Truman 
Scholarship Foundation.Of 1,400 applicants nationwide, only 89 students win the 
$30,000 scholarship each year to attend graduate school in the field of public 
service. 
</P>
<P>
 Watanabe, 21, is enrolled in a semester and summer abroad program in 
Tuebingen, Germany, where she volunteers at a center for Bosnian refugee 
children. The scholarship is awarded to college juniors who maintain a minimum 
grade-point average of 3.75 and demonstrate a dedication to public service. 
</P>
</TEXT>
