<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY FRANCES SMITH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 FORT BRAGG -- A colorful spectrum of cottage industries is showcased at the 
eighth annual Kaleidoscope Festival, 10 a.m.-5 p.m. July 16. Jewelry, clothing 
and other handcrafted items, specialty food products and live entertainment are 
among the offerings. Free.On Laurel and Franklin streets, just east of 
California 1/Main Street. (707) 961-0360. 
</P>
<P>
 SONOMA -- Artists, winemakers, performers, authors and chefs gather to share 
their wares at the ninth annual Salute to the Arts, 11 a.m.-5 p.m. July 16-17 
in downtown's scenic Sonoma Plaza. Tasting ticket packages: $10-$25. 
(Additional taste tickets: $1 each.) (707) 938-1133. 
</P>
<P>
 AVALON -- Swingin', toe-tappin' melodies fill Avalon's Casino Ballroom at the 
23rd annual Catalina Dixieland and Jazz Jamboree, noon-8 p.m. July 23. Igor's 
Jazz Cowboys, Polly Podewell, High Society and the Hyperion Outfall Serenaders 
are among the musicians. Boat/casino packages: $34-$51; casino only: $15-$30. 
(310) 578-5511. 
</P>
<P>
 SAN LUIS OBISPO -- The 24th annual Mozart Festival celebrates Wolfgang Amadeus 
with concerts, lectures and more, July 25-Aug. 7. Clifton Swanson is the music 
director for the event, held at the Mission San Luis Obispo de Tolosa, Church 
of the Nazarene, Cal Poly Theatre, local wineries and other venues. Tickets: 
$12-$32. Series packages available. (805) 781-3010. 
</P>
<P>
 GILROY -- The 16th annual Gilroy Garlic Festival pays tribute to the pungent 
bulb, July 29-31 in Christmas Hill Park. Gourmet garlic foods, arts and crafts, 
cooking demonstrations and more are featured 10 a.m.-7 p.m. Friday; 9 a.m.-5 
p.m. Saturday and Sunday. (408) 842-1625. 
</P>
<P>
 Call listed phone numbers for directions. MARY FRANCES SMITH 
