<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS; 'WHEELCHAIR THROUGH EUROPE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Although she's been in a wheelchair most of her life, Annie Mackin has logged 
four trips to Europe since 1978, and last summer she decided to write a guide 
for other disabled travelers, "Wheelchair Through Europe." 
</P>
<P>
 Mackin, 40, wrote her book with a budget in mind, seeking out accessible 
lodgings from $90 to $110 a night, double. 
</P>
<P>
 European travel, she says "can be difficult, can be challenging, but it's not 
impossible. You miss a lot if you stay home." To obtain a copy of her book, 
send check or money order for $12.95 to Graphic Language Press, P.O. Box 270, 
Cardiff by the Sea, Calif. 92007. 
</P>
