NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS; ON THE ROAD WITH FIDO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 What to do with Rover when you go roving? Six out of 10 pet owners take their 
animals with them, according to the editors of the "Pets-R-Permitted Hotel, 
Motel, Kennel & Petsitter Directory," which has just been updated. 
</P>
<P>
 Editors say the new fifth edition includes more than 10,000 listings of 
lodgings that accommodate pets, kennels and petsitters, among others.To 
purchase a copy, send $10.95 to Pets-R-Permitted Sales, P.O. Box 3930-A, 
Torrance, Calif. 90510. Credit card orders are taken at (800) 274-7297. 
</P>
<P>
 The Traveling Pet Owners of America Assn. also publishes a catalogue of 
lodgings that take pets. The catalogue is $12.95, or free with a $15 annual 
membership, which includes assistance in making pet reservations and a 
quarterly newsletter. Contact: TP Enterprises, P.O. Box 6042, Omaha, Neb. 
68106. 
</P>
<P>
 There's also a bimonthly newsletter called DogGone that looks at topics like 
pet-friendly destinations and animal air travel." A year's subscription is $24. 
Write DogGone, P.O. Box 651155, Vero Beach, Fla., 32965; tel. (407) 569-8434. 
