<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN HELD IN ATTACK ON WOMAN, 81 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An 81-year-old San Fernando woman allegedly stabbed by a transient she had 
befriended was in stable condition Saturday at a local hospital, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police arrested Jim Shepherd, 32, on suspicion of stabbing the woman with a 
kitchen knife in the face, hands and stomach Friday after she let him in her 
home and attempted to prepare him a meal. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman's 82-year-old brother found her at the home they shared on Hagar 
Street just before 3 p.m. Friday. He told police Shepherd came to his law 
office with blood splattered on his shirt and said he had just killed "an enemy 
of God," police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman's brother grew worried after she did not answer his telephone calls, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The brother and sister, whose names were not released, had been friends with 
the transient for the past few years, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Shepherd, who was arrested when he returned a second time to the law office, 
was booked for attempted murder and is being held on $500,000 bail. Police said 
he had a history of mental illness. An arraignment is scheduled for Tuesday. 
</P>
