<P>
BOY, 6, SUFFERS MINOR INJURIES IN HIT-AND-RUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 6-year-old boy received minor injuries Saturday when he darted from an 
apartment and was struck by a hit-and-run driver. 
</P>
<P>
 Benjamin Aguilera of Stanton suffered minor injuries to his left leg in the 
2:06 p.m. hit-and-run, Orange County Sheriff's Lt. Jay Mendez said.The boy was 
taken by paramedics to Anaheim General Hospital, where he was treated and 
released. 
</P>
<P>
 Mendez said the boy ran into the street from the Continental Gardens apartment 
complex, 8101 W. Cerritos Ave., and was struck by an older-model Chevrolet 
Camaro. The male driver did not stop and was last seen driving westbound on 
Cerritos Avenue, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators are looking for the driver and the car. Witnesses were able to 
get only a partial license number of the car. 
