<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHWEST: WEST ADAMS; $700,000 IN LOANS OKD FOR MERCHANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Community Redevelopment Agency has approved a $700,000 loan program to 
help property owners and merchants in the West Adams area who suffered damage 
during the 1992 riots. 
</P>
<P>
 The program will provide low-interest construction or other loans to help 
local businesses retain and expand jobs, and encourage the economic recovery of 
commerical and industrial areas. The project area is roughly bounded by Adams 
Boulevard on the north, Jefferson Boulevard on the south, Western Avenue on the 
west and Normandie Avenue on the east. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 766-9830. 
</P>
</TEXT>
