<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MID-CITY: MID-WILSHIRE; REWARD OFFERED IN ATTACK ON 5 WOMEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GEOFF BOUCHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A $25,000 reward is being offered for information leading to the arrest and 
conviction of two men who assaulted, raped and robbed five women during a home 
invasion. 
</P>
<P>
 The men, armed with handguns, broke into the house in the 800 block of South 
Norton Avenue about 8:30 p.m. May 29, police said.The assailants filled 
pillowcases with household items and stole two cars from the driveway after 
sexually assaulting and beating the five women. 
</P>
<P>
 The reward was established Tuesday by the City Council. Police Detective Mike 
Buttitta said friends of victims are gathering resources and hope to double 
that reward. 
</P>
<P>
 One of the stolen cars was abandoned and set on fire in the 4300 block of 
Exposition Boulevard the morning after the incident, and the second was 
discovered abandoned June 3 in a vacant lot near Washington and Crenshaw 
boulevards. 
</P>
<P>
 Police describe one suspect as a 20- to 24-year-old black male, about 6 feet 
tall and weighing 180 to 200 pounds. Witnesses said he wore black pants and a 
Los Angeles Raiders jacket during the crime. 
</P>
<P>
 The second suspect was described as a thin 17- to 20-year-old black male, 
about 5-feet-9. Witnesses said he was wearing black pants and a black jacket. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone with information about the incident or suspects should call Buttitta at 
(213) 485-2921, or, after-hours and on weekends, the tip hot line at (213) 
485-2504. Tipsters may remain anonymous. GEOFF BOUCHER 
</P>
</TEXT>
